  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The [honest validator guide states](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/validator.md#block-proposal)\r\n> A validator is expected to propose a [SignedBeaconBlock](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#signedbeaconblock) at the beginning of any slot during which is_proposer(state, validator_index) returns True.\r\n\r\nI want to hear opinions on whether we should require clients to not submit a proposal if in their view of their wall clock, their slot has already passed. ",
